</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udionia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dionia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/02 9:03:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=899.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epic faction?</span><hr size=1> Yes, you can jump around finishing different parts if you have the pieces to them. The only one that you really want to do last is the Element of Wind, since you have to go to Sky for that and turning in the pieces spawns the Master of Elements.<br>
<br>
I don't believe our quest givers have a different faction associated with them (like Truespirit for the shaman quest and such), they're either Beta Neutral or on their respective racial mage guild faction. IMO they're on Beta Neutral, since none of the quest text tells of faction raises. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://matt.waggoner.com/orbofmastery.html">The Ultimate Magician's Epic Quest Guide</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, the best site around for help on the epic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><br><i>Signing off from <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.quickJumpTo?id=thecrossroadstavern8833">Zebuxoruk the Ungod</a></i>
